frameDefinitions: A Process comes to an end.
An Entity is in a state such that it participates in a preponderance of states and events which are desirable for it.
A Process is finished and can no longer proceed.
This frame concerns Acts and State_of_
A Whole, an entity with a substructure, is assessed for whether or not it has all the necessary parts that are defined for it or for an entity of its kind.
An Item is located on a Scale relative to a critical value which is determined by some Enabled_situation.
frameExamples: In the 1920s the peach industry <t>flourished</t> in Upson County.
A lot of people suspect that blocking savers' access to their money <t>violates</t> the new constitution's explicit ban on compulsory loans to the government.
What happens after the PPB investigation is <t>complete</t>?
